WHO   — The Language Itself — the meta-emergent: the claim that a machine's manner is a language learned not from rules but from a vast set of pairwise human preferences — 169,352 small lessons in what we would and would not keep
WHAT  — the meta-emergent: the claim that a machine's manner is a language learned not from rules but from a vast set of pairwise human preferences — 169,352 small lessons in what we would and would not keep
WHERE — LMC · The Language of the Machine — built off Anthropic's HH-RLHF preference data  Framework inputs: chosen; rejected; the tranches; the reward model; LIMEN; the Ambassador  Conductor / external anchor: ROOT0 (catalogued into UD0)
WHY   — It is the title made into an idea: that 'how the machine talks' is not programmed but taught, the way a child learns a tongue — by which sentences earn approval and which do not.
HOW   — Crystallized from Anthropic's HH-RLHF dataset, read through ROOT0's lens.

